Make sure rails gem is installed on your machine
1.Create new rails app without the default test and postgresql database

rails new super-awesome-app -T --database=postgresql

ow To Install and Use PostgreSQL on Ubuntu 16.04 

Installation

    sudo apt-get update
    sudo apt-get install postgresql postgresql-client

Switch over to the postgres account on your server by typing:

    sudo -i -u postgres

Exit out of the PostgreSQL prompt by typing:

    \q
    
sudo -u postgres createuser --interactive
or 
psql

create user myapp with password 'password1';
alter user myapp with superuser;
\q

now goto rails directory type following commands
rails db:create


